track_notes: Sommet de Nibles and Cloche de Barles... Starting from Le Forest... Nice trip...

This is a wonderfull place, for eyes and radio! You must park on the small road (not so many room) near the Forest village where is a GSM pylone nearby. The track is easy (yellow paint; it could be some sheep and guard-dog. At the Col 1787m you must Climb some rocks to reach Sommet de Nibles (2 ways possible, easyer on the west-side); much more easy for the Cloche de Barles. The trig point is on the final crest, where you must behave for vertigo. Plenty room for antenna.
Because of a closed road the acces to the starting point was forbidden! we had to walk from the village of Barles. The walk is easy and pleasant, even if it was some snow and little ice on ground.
